article.headline: Longwood 113, Va. Intermont 60
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Ryan Bogan scored 20 points and Antwan Carter notched a double-double to lead Longwood to a 113-60 rout against Virginia-Intermont on Saturday. Carter scored 19 points and grabbed 11 boards for the Lancers (6-6), who shot 51.2 percent from the field (43-for-84) in the game. Dana Smith added 18 points. The Lancers hit 50 percent of their 3-point shots (11 of 22), as Bogan and Kevin Swecker hit three 3-pointers apiece. Longwood was perfect from the free-throw line, making 16-of-16 shots. Jimmie Ross scored 16 points to lead the Cobras (2-12), while Akeen Price added 10. The Cobras shot 38.8 percent from the field (21 of 54). Longwood never trailed in the game, using a 15-0 run with 4:17 left in the first half to grab a 59-29 lead at the break.
